en_793855_0	A group of Student Officers following the Unit Commanders Course (UCC) No-4 at Buttala Officer Career Development Centre (OCDC) as part of their curriculum had the privilege of interacting with the Commander of the Army, Lieutenant General Mahesh Senanayake and Principal Staff Officers (PSOs) at the Army Headquarters to receive a better exposure and understanding on relevant fields this morning (11).
en_793855_1	The 22-member group of UCC Student Officers were interviewed by the panel, headed by the Commander of the Army, Lieutenant General Mahesh Senanayake in order to assess the standards of their knowledge on Commanding Strategies.
en_793855_2	Major General Kumudu Perera, Deputy Chief of Staff, Major General Duminda Keppetiwalana, Director General Infantry, Major General H.G.I Vidyanangda, Quarter Master General, Major General A.M.R Dharmasiri, Director General General Staff, Major General H.R.K.P Peiris, Master General Ordnance, Major General Suraj Bangsajayah, Director General Training, Major General Duminda Sirinaga, Director General Financial Management, Major General Jayantha Seneviratne, Adjutant General, Principal Staff Officers of the Army Headquarters and Colonel Kapila Dolage, Chief Instructor OCDC were also present during the event.
